Huh?

133
00:08:37.183 --> 00:08:40.720  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
If we use these,
we should be able to fight back.

134
00:08:41.053 --> 00:08:42.288  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Yeah, but--

135
00:08:42.555 --> 00:08:46.726  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
But Sato has us beat in terms
of numbers, supplies and experience.

136
00:08:46.993 --> 00:08:51.130  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You want to fight him alone? Heh.
That's funny.

137
00:08:53.866 --> 00:08:57.870  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
So, what is it we should be doing now?

138
00:08:59.772 --> 00:09:01.040  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Working out?

139
00:09:02.108 --> 00:09:03.743  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No, finding allies.

140
00:09:04.310 --> 00:09:08.548  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
What we need are some adults
who can provide us with powerful support.

141
00:09:08.781 --> 00:09:09.715  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[exclaims]

142
00:09:10.750 --> 00:09:11.918  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[tires screeching]

143
00:09:13.786 --> 00:09:15.087  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What are you doing now?!

144
00:09:15.154 --> 00:09:17.290  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Allies, right? I've got an idea!

145
00:09:17.557 --> 00:09:19.959  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Well, explain it first!
-Just leave it to me!

146
00:09:20.860 --> 00:09:21.761  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[sighs]

147
00:09:25.097 --> 00:09:26.098  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
CHECKING SERVERS

148
00:09:26.165 --> 00:09:27.633  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
YOU HAVE NO NEW MESSAGES

149
00:09:27.700 --> 00:09:29.835  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Damn it. Still nothing.

150
00:09:44.817 --> 00:09:48.220  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
They're gone.
But he said he'd keep them locked up.

151
00:09:49.255 --> 00:09:52.692  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You idiot. There's no way
he'd leave them in the same place.

152
00:09:52.758 --> 00:09:54.927  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Don't call me an idiot!
-Well, you are an idiot!

153
00:09:54.994 --> 00:09:59.065  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We came to a place where Sato was?
Do you know how dangerous that is?

154
00:09:59.131 --> 00:10:01.000  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What does danger have to do with it?!

155
00:10:02.201 --> 00:10:03.102  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[sighs]

156
00:10:05.304 --> 00:10:06.205  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[phone beeps]

157
00:10:07.206 --> 00:10:09.842  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
YOU HAVE ONE NEW MESSAGE

158
00:10:09.909 --> 00:10:12.378  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Thank God. Finally.

159
00:10:14.146 --> 00:10:15.715  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What's that e-mail?

160
00:10:16.082 --> 00:10:17.883  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Before they found me,

161
00:10:17.950 --> 00:10:21.087  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I ordered a background check
on the Ajin Control Commission.

162
00:10:21.354 --> 00:10:22.722  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
This is it.

163
00:10:26.125 --> 00:10:30.062  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
One of them is a pretty interesting guy.

164
00:10:30.129 --> 00:10:32.231  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
BACKGROUND REPORT

165
00:10:32.298 --> 00:10:34.033  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Nakano] That guy...

166
00:10:39.805 --> 00:10:41.941  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Tosaki] We've expanded the search
to other prefectures,

167
00:10:42.008 --> 00:10:46.312  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
including Kanagawa, Chiba and Saitama,

168
00:10:46.879 --> 00:10:49.181  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
but we've found no leads
regarding Sato's whereabouts.

169
00:10:49.982 --> 00:10:53.719  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
As for countermeasures, we plan
to capture him when he comes to attack.

170
00:10:53.786 --> 00:10:56.789  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Dr. Wakai is the first person
on his hit list.

171
00:10:57.089 --> 00:11:01.293  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I've told the police to treat this as
if they were protecting a head of state.

172
00:11:01.360 --> 00:11:04.130  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm sure you understand, Tosaki.

173
00:11:06.065 --> 00:11:11.437  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
If I were to be killed, that would be
the end of your worthless life as well.

174
00:11:13.873 --> 00:11:15.107  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Yes, sir.

175
00:11:16.108 --> 00:11:17.843  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
NAME: YUU TOSAKI

176
00:11:20.212 --> 00:11:21.113  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[laughs]

177
00:11:21.180 --> 00:11:24.183  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
This is good stuff, Nakano.
Very interesting.

178
00:11:24.950 --> 00:11:29.188  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
His fiancée is in a coma, and he's footing
the medical bills himself.

179
00:11:30.923 --> 00:11:33.826  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
And it's not an amount
he can easily pay off.

180
00:11:35.728 --> 00:11:41.033  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>He's got a reason to stop Sato</i>
<i>and protect his own position.</i>

181
00:11:42.902 --> 00:11:43.803  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[sighs]

182
00:11:44.136 --> 00:11:47.473  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Most importantly,
his lover is his weakness.

183
00:11:48.340 --> 00:11:49.742  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We can use that.

184
00:11:49.875 --> 00:11:50.776  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[grunts]

185
00:11:51.043 --> 00:11:52.778  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
How is this fun for you?

186
00:11:59.018 --> 00:12:00.019  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Mr. Tosaki.

187
00:12:02.054 --> 00:12:04.356  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It's almost time for the council meeting.

188
00:12:07.993 --> 00:12:10.296  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Those damn Ajin...

189
00:12:12.331 --> 00:12:14.100  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[laughing]

190
00:12:18.237 --> 00:12:19.939  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[woman] <i>Yuu...</i>

191
00:12:20.439 --> 00:12:22.041  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Hey, Yuu.

192
00:12:24.076 --> 00:12:27.012  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Won't you quit smoking?
-Not that again.

193
00:12:27.079 --> 00:12:28.247  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I know.

194
00:12:28.881 --> 00:12:32.151  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
But I want us to be together
for as long as possible.

195
00:12:34.286 --> 00:12:35.988  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[laughing]

196
00:12:37.490 --> 00:12:41.127  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
No matter what happens,
there has to be a chance.

197
00:12:45.097 --> 00:12:47.032  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Let's go, Shimomura.

198
00:12:47.166 --> 00:12:48.934  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[phone ringing]

199
00:12:52.505 --> 00:12:54.373  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
INCOMING CALL
UNKNOWN CALLER

200
00:12:58.277 --> 00:12:59.545  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[man over phone] <i>Turn on the TV.</i>

201
00:13:00.045 --> 00:13:02.281  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Who is this? How did you get this number?

202
00:13:02.348 --> 00:13:04.850  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Just turn on the TV. Now.</i>

203
00:13:08.154 --> 00:13:09.822  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[woman over phone]
<i>The high-speed pursuit</i>

204
00:13:09.889 --> 00:13:13.025  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>between the police</i>
<i>and a stolen vehicle continues.</i>

205
00:13:13.092 --> 00:13:16.095  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>We've been told that the fugitive Ajin,</i>
<i>Kei Nagai, is aboard...</i>

206
00:13:16.162 --> 00:13:17.963  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Kei Nagai?!
-[Nagai] <i>That's right.</i>

207
00:13:18.330 --> 00:13:21.400  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>And you should be able to guess</i>
<i>where we're going!</i>

208
00:13:23.135 --> 00:13:24.036  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Uh--

209
00:13:24.103 --> 00:13:26.472  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Damn it! The battery died!

210
00:13:27.273 --> 00:13:31.343  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[woman] <i>Police have already warned locals,</i>
<i>asking them to remain indoors.</i>

211
00:13:31.410 --> 00:13:33.045  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Wait, that street...

212
00:13:33.112 --> 00:13:35.447  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>They are moving to apprehend the Ajin</i>
<i>and his accomplice.</i>

213
00:13:35.514 --> 00:13:37.550  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That bastard...

214
00:13:38.984 --> 00:13:42.254  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
TOUTO UNIVERSITY HOSPITAL

215
00:13:42.388 --> 00:13:43.856  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[tires screeching]

216
00:13:57.269 --> 00:14:00.973  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You've got your earpieces and fake IDs?
I'm going in through the rear.

217
00:14:01.040 --> 00:14:02.107  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Copy that.

218
00:14:02.174 --> 00:14:04.877  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
The suspects have entered the hospital.
We'll make the arrest.

219
00:14:04.944 --> 00:14:07.012  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We'll go in from the front and the back!

220
00:14:07.079 --> 00:14:08.280  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[car approaching]

221
00:14:09.081 --> 00:14:10.249  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What--?

222
00:14:11.483 --> 00:14:13.285  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Who are you?

223
00:14:14.420 --> 00:14:17.590  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Excuse me, sir!
-All of you wait outside. We're going in.

224
00:14:19.491 --> 00:14:20.626  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[both panting]

225
00:14:21.594 --> 00:14:24.063  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What the hell, Nagai?! What's your plan?!

226
00:14:24.129 --> 00:14:26.632  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-I'll explain later! You hide!
-Where?!

227
00:14:26.899 --> 00:14:31.537  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I don't care! Just use your ghost to stop
his men when they come to capture me!

228
00:14:31.604 --> 00:14:35.307  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Ghost? You mean, those black monsters?!
I can't make those things!

229
00:14:35.941 --> 00:14:38.210  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-That isn't funny.
-I'm serious!

230
00:14:38.277 --> 00:14:40.946  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
The first time I saw one,
it totally freaked me out!

231
00:14:41.013 --> 00:14:43.482  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Whatever, just hide.
This'll be harder if you're around!

232
00:14:43.549 --> 00:14:44.516  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Huh?

233
00:14:47.887 --> 00:14:50.289  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Let's go.
-What do you think he's after?

234
00:14:50.356 --> 00:14:51.657  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Maybe it's revenge.

235
00:14:52.524 --> 00:14:55.427  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Or maybe Nagai is involved with Sato.

236
00:14:55.494 --> 00:14:56.962  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Shimomura] Isn't this dangerous?

237
00:14:58.063 --> 00:14:59.331  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What is your job?

238
00:15:00.299 --> 00:15:01.901  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
My job is to...

239
00:15:03.235 --> 00:15:04.670  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It's to protect you.

240
00:15:07.306 --> 00:15:10.175  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
If I die, there's no future
for you either.

241
00:15:11.343 --> 00:15:14.046  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
So fight, for your own sake.

242
00:15:16.649 --> 00:15:19.285  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[woman] There's a solemn atmosphere
hanging over the scene!

243
00:15:20.019 --> 00:15:23.389  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
The police have surrounded the building
and started evacuating,

244
00:15:23.455 --> 00:15:25.658  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
possibly out of fear
that this is Ajin terrorism!

245
00:15:37.169 --> 00:15:42.141  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Want to know the truth? I never wanted
to see your face again, Mr. Tosaki.

246
00:15:42.207 --> 00:15:46.545  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Too bad, because you and I will be seeing
each other every day from now on,

247
00:15:46.612 --> 00:15:48.113  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
right through the glass.

248
00:15:48.180 --> 00:15:49.615  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I want to talk.

249
00:15:49.682 --> 00:15:51.283  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Let's keep this civil.

250
00:15:51.350 --> 00:15:54.653  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Then why don't we go outside?
It's a beautiful day.

251
00:15:55.454 --> 00:16:01.393  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You try anything and I'll summon my ghost.
It will attack without orders.

252
00:16:01.460 --> 00:16:05.064  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Even if you knock me out,
that won't stop it from doing damage.

253
00:16:06.398 --> 00:16:07.299  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[scoffs]

254
00:16:07.967 --> 00:16:10.069  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Nagai]
<i>It probably won't end well for you.</i>

255
00:16:11.170 --> 00:16:12.304  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And especially...

256
00:16:13.372 --> 00:16:16.008  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
not for this woman right here.

257
00:16:16.976 --> 00:16:19.345  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I swear... I'll kill you.

258
00:16:20.245 --> 00:16:21.113  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[grunting]

259
00:16:21.180 --> 00:16:22.247  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[gasps]

260
00:16:23.549 --> 00:16:24.450  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[screams]

261
00:16:25.718 --> 00:16:26.585  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Huh?

262
00:16:28.988 --> 00:16:30.456  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Wait! Don't shoot!!

263
00:16:30.522 --> 00:16:33.759  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Nagai! You don't have to do this!
-Stay out of it, Nakano!

264
00:16:34.026 --> 00:16:35.327  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Sir...? Do we shoot?!

265
00:16:35.394 --> 00:16:36.495  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Kill me if you can!

266
00:16:37.429 --> 00:16:38.330  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[grunting]

267
00:16:41.200 --> 00:16:42.634  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Don't shoot!

268
00:16:42.701 --> 00:16:44.203  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Idiot!

269
00:16:45.037 --> 00:16:46.338  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Nagai!
-Kill her!

270
00:16:47.206 --> 00:16:48.273  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Stop!

271
00:16:56.315 --> 00:16:59.118  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm getting sick of this.

272
00:17:03.555 --> 00:17:04.690  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That thing...

273
00:17:05.691 --> 00:17:08.327  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
always does the opposite
of what I command.

274
00:17:09.028 --> 00:17:10.095  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Nakano sighs]

275
00:17:11.530 --> 00:17:12.698  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What is it you want?

276
00:17:16.435 --> 00:17:17.369  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It's summer.

277
00:17:21.140 --> 00:17:23.275  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Sunlight would pour into the classroom.

278
00:17:24.476 --> 00:17:27.312  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
My sweaty hands would stick
to my notebook.

279
00:17:28.414 --> 00:17:32.718  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>It was quiet and boring,</i>
<i>but it was civilized.</i>

280
00:17:37.656 --> 00:17:40.359  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You never wanted it this way either,
did you?

281
00:17:40.692 --> 00:17:43.062  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No. And it's all your fault.

282
00:17:43.228 --> 00:17:48.534  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Wrong! It's not my fault this happened.
And it's not your fault either.

283
00:17:49.168 --> 00:17:50.569  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We're the same.

284
00:17:54.506 --> 00:17:56.442  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I came here to make a deal with you.

285
00:17:56.508 --> 00:17:58.677  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
As if I could trust an Ajin!

286
00:17:59.078 --> 00:18:02.381  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I don't really understand what's going on,
but I do know one thing.

287
00:18:02.448 --> 00:18:05.651  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We plan to take down Sato,
no matter what it takes!

288
00:18:05.851 --> 00:18:08.654  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
For her sake as well. So, if you arrest--

289
00:18:08.720 --> 00:18:11.790  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
So, listen, we'll be your pawns!

290
00:18:12.324 --> 00:18:14.126  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Your immortal soldiers!

291
00:18:14.760 --> 00:18:16.295  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That's right! So...

292
00:18:17.362 --> 00:18:18.230  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Huh?

293
00:18:24.203 --> 00:18:25.237  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What's the situation?

294
00:18:25.871 --> 00:18:28.807  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
The suspects have been arrested.
We'll take care of the rest.

295
00:18:30.442 --> 00:18:33.579  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[officer] By the way,
was it really Kei Nagai?

296
00:18:35.114 --> 00:18:38.250  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
No, it was someone else.
Just looked like him.

297
00:18:44.857 --> 00:18:46.391  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Oh--
-Ah?

298
00:18:47.292 --> 00:18:49.194  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
SEPTEMBER 3RD

299
00:18:49.261 --> 00:18:52.598  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, summer vacation was over.

300
00:19:01.740 --> 00:19:06.512  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
MESSAGE FROM SATO

301
00:19:06.578 --> 00:19:07.880  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, it's started.

302
00:19:09.882 --> 00:19:13.719  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Hello. We meet once again. It's Sato.

303
00:19:17.422 --> 00:19:22.628  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
As far as I know, the government has
not yet responded to my demands.

304
00:19:23.529 --> 00:19:25.898  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
So... I decided to get started.

305
00:19:26.365 --> 00:19:28.367  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[muffled whimpering]

306
00:19:31.436 --> 00:19:35.240  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
That's right, with the top
of the batting order, Dr. Wakai.

307
00:19:39.478 --> 00:19:41.680  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
All right, batter up.

308
00:19:42.247 --> 00:19:43.582  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[muffled screaming]

309
00:19:44.683 --> 00:19:45.551  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[gunshot]

310
00:19:49.388 --> 00:19:51.423  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
And this is the beginning
of the countdown.

311
00:19:52.891 --> 00:19:58.297  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>When the second wave finishes,</i>
<i>we'll move on to the third wave.</i>

312
00:20:00.766 --> 00:20:04.503  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>The third... and final wave.</i>

313
00:20:07.372 --> 00:20:09.641  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I am going to take over this country.

314
00:20:10.976 --> 00:20:12.878  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You think it's just some corny dream?

315
00:20:15.247 --> 00:20:16.248  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I will do it.

316
00:20:17.783 --> 00:20:18.684  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Count on it.

317
00:20:21.887 --> 00:20:24.256  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
TO BE CONTINUED

318
00:20:25.324 --> 00:20:28.393  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>♪ I'm tired of this one already, so ♪</i>

319
00:20:28.460 --> 00:20:31.663  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>♪ I'll trade it ♪</i>

320
00:20:31.730 --> 00:20:36.868  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>♪ For your ordinary one ♪</i>

321
00:20:38.003 --> 00:20:44.409  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>♪ A shiny holy card ♪</i>

322
00:20:44.509 --> 00:20:49.982  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>♪ For a grainy paper card ♪</i>

323
00:20:50.782 --> 00:20:54.886  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>♪ You can see them all ♪</i>

324
00:20:57.322 --> 00:21:01.660  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>♪ When you come to my house ♪</i>

325
00:21:01.727 --> 00:21:07.766  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>♪ So two of us</i>
<i>In the corner of the schoolyard ♪</i>

326
00:21:07.833 --> 00:21:09.935  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>♪ While the wind blows ♪</i>

327
00:21:10.002 --> 00:21:14.406  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>♪ I might be able to say it now ♪</i>

328
00:21:16.508 --> 00:21:22.714  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>♪ Words I've never said to anyone ♪</i>

329
00:21:22.781 --> 00:21:29.021  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>♪ "Won't you come and play,</i>
<i>I'll be nice" ♪</i>

330
00:21:29.288 --> 00:21:34.993  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>♪ "I'll give you anything, see" ♪</i>

331
00:21:35.661 --> 00:21:38.430  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>♪ "Be my friend ♪</i>

332
00:21:38.497 --> 00:21:45.337  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>♪ Always" ♪♪</i>

